You will be responsible for:

assisting in IT solutions from business initiative, system planning, tender preparation to implementation, change management, production deployment, and handling vendor related activities;
performing implementation activities including but not limited to business processes mapping, advice for operations improvement, requirements gathering and analysis, system design and analysis, knowledge transfer, and change management processes;
ensuring all applications and solutions operate according to the Authority’s IT standards and industrial best practices, and in a stable and effective manner with good quality, including but not limited to the architecture, coding standards, information security;
coordinating post-implementation support and preventative maintenance activities with vendors, IT and business users; and
keeping up with the latest technology trend, continuous measure, propose and explore enhancement opportunity to drive operational excellence and effectiveness.

You should:

possess a recognised university degree in Computer Science, Information Technology or equivalent;
have minimum 5 years of relevant IT experience, preferably in sizable organisation;
have any prior experience in both functional and technical perspective of Oracle ERP/ Salesforce CRM/ Ticketing System/ Payment Gateway/ Venue and Event Management/ Facility Management/ Workforce Management/ Digital Signage/ E-Tendering/ E-Commerce/ Website Content Management/ Drupal would be an advantage;
have knowledge of and experience in digital transformation, mobile app, and cloud technology (AWS or similar) would be an advantage;
have solid experience in application development and system design for technology initiatives using a hybrid mix of traditional and agile SDLC methodologies;
have strong problem-solving skills, a team player, self-motivated and capable to lead a small team; be innovative with strong enthusiasm in exploring new technologies; and
be proficient in written and spoken English and Chinese.

For interested parties, please submit your application with detailed CV on or before 24 January 2022. Applicants are encouraged to submit their applications as soon as possible.  The review of applications will continue until the post is filled.

Data collected will only be used for job application processing. Your data may be accessed by our appointed recruitment consultants who have agreed to keep confidence of all personal data in not less than the standards applicable to us. Applicants not being invited for interview within 4 weeks from the submission date may assume their applications unsuccessful.

All related information will be kept up to 24 months and all personal data will be destroyed afterwards.

